[[the]] [[emperor]] [[has]] [[no]] [[clothes]]
#([[idiomatic]]) alludes to the situation where no-one is willing to point out an obvious fault for fear of appearing silly.
===Etymology===
*Based on the [[folk tale]], “The Emperor Has No Clothes,” by Hans Christian Andersen, where [[weaver]]s claim they can weave cloth that only smart people can see, and the townsfolk are afraid to admit that they can't see it.